1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:03,810
(Episode 109)

2
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:16,590
(Chang, Sil)

3
00:00:19,090 --> 00:00:21,490
"Chang. Sil."

4
00:00:25,330 --> 00:00:28,030
(Chang, Sil)

5
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,070
Oh my, Seo Rin!

6
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,510
What is this?

7
00:00:35,310 --> 00:00:38,940
This is the necklace my grandfather gave
to his lost daughter, isn't it?

8
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,910
Then why do you have both of them?

9
00:00:42,550 --> 00:00:44,480
No. It's nothing. Give it to me, Seo Rin.

10
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:48,990
Wait, are you...

11
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:51,490
Grandfather's daughter?

12
00:00:54,690 --> 00:00:55,690
Oh, shit!

13
00:01:01,530 --> 00:01:05,440
No, that's ridiculous.
How could I be Father's daughter?

14
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:07,940
- That's impossible.
- Then what is it?

15
00:01:08,370 --> 00:01:10,210
I'm asking you,
what is that necklace in there?

16
00:01:10,510 --> 00:01:13,780
You were trying to fit the two pieces
because you're Ma Eun Hye, weren't you?

17
00:01:14,580 --> 00:01:15,580
Oh, shit!

18
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:17,180
Seo Rin.

19
00:01:17,950 --> 00:01:20,950
Seo Rin can't say anything right now.
No. This can't happen.

20
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:27,430
But what if...

21
00:01:27,990 --> 00:01:31,900
What happens if Mom really is
Grandfather's long-lost daughter?

22
00:01:34,930 --> 00:01:35,930
Ma Seo Rin.

23
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:40,210
Mom, are you really
Grandfather's daughter? You're not, right?

24
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:41,370
Of course not.

25
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:46,080
Then what is that necklace?
Who did you steal it from?

26
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:48,550
I'm telling Grandfather right now.

27
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:53,220
- Mom!
- Snap out of it. I said, snap out of it!

28
00:01:53,550 --> 00:01:57,220
What on earth are you talking about?
What would you even tell Grandfather?

29
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:59,290
What sort of nonsense
are you planning to spout?

30
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:03,930
- Ma Seo Rin. You're crazy, aren't you?
- Why did you hit me?

31
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:08,470
I've lost my mind?
I saw it. I saw it with my own two eyes.

32
00:02:08,530 --> 00:02:10,130
The two necklace pieces
fitting together as one.

33
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,300
You saw it wrong.

34
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,910
Why have you been so out of it lately?

35
00:02:15,170 --> 00:02:17,610
You can't even see things straight,
and now you're just being stubborn.

36
00:02:17,710 --> 00:02:20,480
Then what's the necklace
you shoved into your pocket so quickly?

37
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:24,380
Take it out. Right now. Take it out
and we'll see if I was imagining things.

38
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,520
You're unbelievable.

39
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,350
It's not a big deal.

40
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,290
You know that fake daughter
who came to see Father the other day?

41
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:33,630
She left her fake necklace behind,

42
00:02:33,790 --> 00:02:37,460
so I was just comparing it to the real one
to see the difference. That's all.

43
00:02:37,530 --> 00:02:38,960
You expect me to believe that?

44
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,630
Ma Seo Rin. Get a grip.

45
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,840
Think about it.
If I were Father's biological daughter,

46
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,140
why would I be suffering this humiliation
under Oh Jang Mi?

47
00:02:48,470 --> 00:02:51,910
I'd tell Father I'm his daughter.
Immediately.

48
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:56,180
Then what about the matching necklaces?
What was that?

49
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:09,590
Seo Rin, think about it.

50
00:03:10,130 --> 00:03:14,730
If I were his daughter,
I'd have presented Jun Ho as his grandson.

51
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:16,370
Why would I still be hiding him?

52
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,070
Fine, let's say this.

53
00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:22,240
If I knew who owned that necklace,
like you claim,

54
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:24,240
why would I bother hiding it...

55
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:27,080
when your grandpa is searching
desperately for her?

56
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:30,210
It's because I don't know
who his real daughter is!

57
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:34,190
No matter what excuse she gives,
something about this doesn't add up.

58
00:03:34,650 --> 00:03:36,250
Mom must know something.

59
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:49,800
(Chang)

60
00:04:05,380 --> 00:04:08,920
This is driving me crazy. Seo Rin saw it.
What am I going to do?

61
00:04:09,690 --> 00:04:11,720
She didn't look like she bought it at all.

62
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,360
Darn it.

63
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:18,300
That Jung Suk Hee is...

64
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:21,100
the Chairman's daughter
must never come out.

65
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:26,270
For that to happen,
this necklace must never be found.

66
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,440
Ever.

67
00:04:30,310 --> 00:04:31,540
Mom, let's eat.

68
00:04:32,210 --> 00:04:34,210
Looks like Tae Sook
left early again today.

69
00:04:34,850 --> 00:04:37,380
She's opening a second location.
She must be busy.

70
00:04:37,850 --> 00:04:39,150
Bo Ra, time to eat.

71
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:42,350
Bo Ra is drawing with Suk Hee right now.

72
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:46,190
Bo Ra, you're getting better and better.
You're a great artist.

73
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:49,730
My pictures are getting prettier
because I'm copying how Grandma draws.

74
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:54,430
What? You're not wearing
that necklace today?

75
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,530
Grandma, why aren't you wearing
your necklace?

76
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:59,100
You said you can't ever lose it.

77
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:02,070
No, that's not right.
Suk Hee has her necklace.

78
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:07,780
Mom, didn't you just take it off for a bit
and forget where you put it?

79
00:05:07,910 --> 00:05:09,710
Suk Hee didn't take her necklace off.

80
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,120
Suk Hee's necklace is gone.

81
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:14,390
That's true. I've never seen you
take it off before, Mom.

82
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:19,290
Grandma, you said you'd take care of it
because it's precious.

83
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:21,430
This can't be happening.
Suk Hee's necklace is gone.

84
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:25,530
- My necklace!
- Mom.

85
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:27,030
Goodness.

86
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:28,930
- Just a minute.
- Stay here.

87
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,640
My grandma is so scatterbrained.

88
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:38,010
Come on out, Suk Hee's necklace.
You can't have gone far.

89
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:40,040
I can't lose you.

90
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:42,410
If it were on the floor,
we would've spotted it by now.

91
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,250
Or maybe you dropped it outside?

92
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,750
When you went to the market,
or when you went to pick up Bo Ra.

93
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:50,120
No. Mom's been staying home
or at the store lately.

94
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:52,360
Suk Hee's necklace is gone.

95
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,230
Come on out, necklace.

96
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:58,330
You and Tae Pyung go eat.
I'll search everywhere in here again.

97
00:05:58,430 --> 00:06:01,530
- If it's not here, I'll check outside.
- Where in the world could it be?

98
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:04,140
It's not like it grew legs
and walked away.

99
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:07,510
- Help me look!
- Look everywhere!

100
00:06:08,170 --> 00:06:09,170
Wait.

101
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:11,140
Here it is.

102
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:14,780
I found it. No wonder we missed it.

103
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:18,220
You found the necklace.
Good girl, Jang Mi.

104
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:21,120
Impressive. You've got a sharp eye.

105
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:24,090
Mom, let me wipe it clean
and put it back on for you.

106
00:06:26,690 --> 00:06:30,660
Wait. This isn't Suk Hee's.

107
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:34,030
Yes it is, Mom. Look,
it even has the "Chang" character.

108
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:38,240
- No. This isn't Suk Hee's necklace.
- Mom, come on.

109
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,200
I guess you're confused
because you used to...

110
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,870
wear that necklace all the time,
and then you lost it.

111
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:45,910
Mom, why don't you wear this one
until we find the real one, okay?

112
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,850
This isn't Suk Hee's necklace.

113
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,620
My necklace is gone.

114
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,160
Grandfather.

115
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:05,960
Why are you so tight-lipped
when it comes to my aunt?

116
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,470
Is there a reason?

117
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:13,470
Yes, honey. Why do you keep it bottled up
and suffer in silence?

118
00:07:13,970 --> 00:07:16,510
We're all dying to know, honey.

119
00:07:16,570 --> 00:07:19,310
What is there to be so curious about?

120
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:22,110
She's the child I had to bury in my heart.

121
00:07:22,450 --> 00:07:23,710
To dredge up all those painful memories...

122
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:26,580
and just go on and on about it?
Do you think that's easy?

123
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:30,450
Even so, I've been feeling a little hurt
by you lately, honey.

124
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,920
Yes, speaking.

125
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:33,490
Gosh.

126
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:37,460
If he finds his biological daughter,
that would make me her stepmother.

127
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,870
And yet he treats me
like I'm completely invisible.

128
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:43,730
Stepmother? In your dreams, Yeom San Wol.

129
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:47,310
- What?
- What are you glaring at? Am I wrong?

130
00:07:47,910 --> 00:07:51,440
You wouldn't even be a royal concubine.
You'd be a lowly palace maid.

131
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,440
How dare you try
to get a piece of the pie?

132
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:54,910
You should know your place.

133
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,080
What did you just say to me?

134
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,250
Mom.

135
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:00,890
Shit.

136
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:04,590
I didn't have an appetite to begin with.
What's with the fighting at dinner?

137
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:05,820
I'm not eating.

138
00:08:07,290 --> 00:08:09,630
A palace maid? A palace maid?

139
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,260
Unbelievable.

140
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:19,240
The wrench...

141
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,140
This area is full of hikers
using the main trails.

142
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:25,140
So he couldn't possibly have hidden
the weapon here.

143
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:28,050
Someone might have seen him
and gotten suspicious.

144
00:08:28,150 --> 00:08:30,210
So it must be somewhere deep in the woods.

145
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:34,020
But we can't search this whole mountain
for one wrench,

146
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:36,650
- so what now?
- Seo Rin put something on the USB.

147
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:41,860
She mapped the culprit's last stop by GPS,
along with the estimated coordinates.

148
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:43,660
And she pinpointed it
to be right around here.

149
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:45,700
Around here?

150
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:50,170
But GPS isn't accurate in the mountains.
How can we pinpoint the exact location?

151
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,500
We'll have to get inside
the culprit's head.

152
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:53,940
The culprit's psychology?

153
00:08:54,170 --> 00:08:57,440
Why would he bury a weapon
he could've just tossed in a river?

154
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:02,980
Maybe he buried it because he thought
he might need it as leverage later?

155
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:05,820
But Manager Lee seemed completely devoted
to Chae Hwa Young.

156
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:07,290
Manager Lee is only human.

157
00:09:08,090 --> 00:09:09,920
Because he's been by her side
watching her all this time,

158
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,220
he definitely would have needed
some leverage.

159
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:15,360
That's true.
Seeing how she killed Ssangkal,

160
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,830
he must have known her true colors
for a long time.

161
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:20,800
So to make it easy for himself
to find later,

162
00:09:20,930 --> 00:09:25,740
he'd subconsciously use a clear landmark
as a reference point.

163
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:29,040
- That makes sense.
- The spot Seo Rin marked is...

164
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:32,480
probably a large tree or a big rock,
don't you think?

165
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,080
You're probably right.

166
00:09:34,510 --> 00:09:36,850
I didn't understand
what Seo Rin had marked,

167
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:39,420
but now that you mention it,
it all makes sense.

168
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,050
Let's go check it out
together this weekend.

169
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:45,820
- Okay, honey?
- Oh my. What's gotten into you?

170
00:09:45,990 --> 00:09:47,090
That was so cringey.

171
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:51,300
Cringey? What are you talking about?
We're married. Have you forgotten?

172
00:09:51,830 --> 00:09:53,330
I don't know what to do with you, wifey.

173
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,570
Hey! Stop it, it's embarrassing.

174
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,910
Something's been bothering me,

175
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:05,040
so I came to talk to you about it.

176
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:06,540
All right.

177
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:09,950
Did you remember something about Eun Hye?

178
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,350
It's not that.

179
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:15,820
You know that woman we saw the other day?

180
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,320
That woman?

181
00:10:18,690 --> 00:10:19,890
Strangely,

182
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:22,560
she has my sister's habit.

183
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:26,060
My sister had this habit
of holding both her ears, remember?

184
00:10:26,430 --> 00:10:27,430
She did.

185
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,240
Whenever Seong Sil was flustered,
she would do that.

186
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:35,370
- She did have that habit.
- I mean, on that day...

187
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:40,010
Chairman, you have a visitor.

188
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,110
A visitor?

189
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:43,880
Who is it?

190
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:57,060
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

191
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,600
- What are you doing here?
- It's Grandfather!

192
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:07,670
I ruined Grandma's clothes.
Suk Hee ruined Grandma's clothes.

193
00:11:08,910 --> 00:11:10,140
I'm sorry.

194
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:13,840
I'm already worried
about his high blood pressure.

195
00:11:14,210 --> 00:11:17,680
Imagine telling him
that some simple-minded stranger...

196
00:11:18,380 --> 00:11:21,020
has the same habit as his late wife.

197
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:25,090
Father would be so devastated,
he'd collapse on the spot.

198
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:29,830
And who is this little one?

199
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:33,100
Hello, I'm Yeon Bo Ra
from the Little Chick Class.

200
00:11:33,430 --> 00:11:34,500
Yeon Bo Ra?

201
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,540
You're so adorable. Yeon Bo Ra?

202
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,500
Where are you from, sweetie?

203
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:43,410
Did you come with your grandma here?

204
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:46,580
Yes, we're from Suk Hee's Side Dishes.

205
00:11:47,410 --> 00:11:50,010
My grandma is a very nice person.

206
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:56,320
Since the little one is here,
bring out some fruit or something for her.

207
00:11:57,220 --> 00:12:01,060
- And get them some tea or something.
- Grandfather.

208
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:02,990
This is delicious.

209
00:12:04,730 --> 00:12:07,000
Grandfather, I'm sorry.

210
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,070
Mom!

211
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:18,780
Let go of me! I'm not letting that witch
get away with this.

212
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:20,980
Just because I always
bite my tongue and take it...

213
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:25,620
You think you can treat me like dirt,
but there's a limit!

214
00:12:26,450 --> 00:12:30,220
Am I still the one who carries your bags
and helps you get dressed?

215
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,690
Do I look like your gofer?

216
00:12:33,190 --> 00:12:35,530
Yeom San Wol, have you lost your mind?

217
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:40,430
- Who do you think you are, yelling at me?
- It's nothing.

218
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:43,830
I think Mom's just in a bad mood
and taking it out on you.

219
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:48,610
What did you call me earlier?
What? A palace maid?

220
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:51,210
- You think words have no consequences?
- Are you serious?

221
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,240
If you're not a servant,
what are you then?

222
00:12:53,610 --> 00:12:55,650
Where do you get off
with this pathetic stepmother act?

223
00:12:55,710 --> 00:12:58,220
And what's to stop me
from becoming her stepmother?

224
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:01,320
- You've really lost it!
- Oh my!

225
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,020
Chae Hwa Young,
what do you think you're doing?

226
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,630
"Chae Hwa Young?"
I've had just about enough of you!

227
00:13:08,690 --> 00:13:09,760
Oh my goodness!

228
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:13,200
What are you doing to my daughter?
You keep looking down on me?

229
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:16,400
- I can't believe this!
- How dare you!

230
00:13:16,470 --> 00:13:19,000
- Get your hands off her!
- Hey!

231
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:20,640
- Let go!
- You, get over here!

232
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:21,710
Oh my!

233
00:13:21,970 --> 00:13:24,540
Hey! You two got a death wish?

234
00:13:24,610 --> 00:13:28,880
Oh my, you're going to hit me with that?
I'm sorry. I was completely out of line.

235
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:32,680
Please put that down and calm down.

236
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:33,680
Put that down.

237
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:36,990
Try pulling a stunt like that again.
I'll make you regret it!

238
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,720
Both of you.

239
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:43,660
If you defy me again,
I won't let it slide.

240
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:48,070
Got it? Just remember that
I hold your lives in my hands. Got it?

241
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:56,710
Gosh, darn it.

242
00:13:58,310 --> 00:13:59,310
Gosh.

243
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:03,880
<i>Three bears live in a house</i>

244
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:06,120
<i>Papa Bear, Mama Bear</i>

245
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,520
<i>- Baby Bear</i>
- What? When did Jung Suk Hee get here?

246
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,460
This is driving me crazy.

247
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:14,120
A biological daughter and her father
together like that?

248
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:15,690
This can't happen, Jung Suk Hee.

249
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:19,060
I'm talking about that woman from earlier.

250
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:23,870
Her looks and her mannerisms
were so much like my sister's.

251
00:14:23,930 --> 00:14:27,370
What? What on earth are you talking about?

252
00:14:27,570 --> 00:14:29,570
Whenever my sister got flustered,

253
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:32,980
she'd grab both of her earlobes
like this...

254
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,580
and hold them to cool down.
It was a habit of hers.

255
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:40,720
<i>So proud, so proud!</i>

256
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:43,950
Wait.

257
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:46,690
Chae Hwa Young is mean. She's a thief.

258
00:14:48,060 --> 00:14:50,530
You brought side dishes, right?
Let me see them.

259
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,170
These are for Grandfather.
Suk Hee made them all.

260
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,180
Don't you know the Chairman
can't stand you?

261
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:10,250
So why do you keep coming here
to bother him?

262
00:15:10,580 --> 00:15:11,580
Get lost.

263
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:14,490
- I said, get lost!
- I have to see Tok Hee.

264
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:18,520
- I miss Tok Hee.
- Tok Hee?

265
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,290
Seo Rin's not here. She went out.

266
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:23,330
Besides, what makes you think
Seo Rin wants to see someone like you?

267
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:27,630
- You're so dense. Can't you take a hint?
- No.

268
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:32,040
- Tok Hee likes me.
- After the mess you caused last time,

269
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,840
who said you were welcome here?
Why are you back to cause another scene?

270
00:15:35,370 --> 00:15:36,410
Get out of here, now! Or else!

271
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,180
The thief is bad.

272
00:15:40,810 --> 00:15:42,550
Grandfather, I'm sorry.

273
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,880
Grandma.

274
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:48,420
What did my grandma do wrong?
Why are you treating her like this?

275
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:50,250
Who do you think you are?
What a little brat.

276
00:15:51,020 --> 00:15:52,260
Take your grandma and get out of here.

277
00:16:02,570 --> 00:16:04,470
I can't trust Oh Jang Mi
or Chae Hwa Young.

278
00:16:05,170 --> 00:16:06,370
And I trusted her, my own mother.

279
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:10,010
If I don't get her full support
for marrying Jun Ho,

280
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,210
I'm not just going to sit idly by.

281
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,080
I have no use for a mother
who won't even support my love life.

282
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:20,750
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

283
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:24,890
If you're not too busy,
would you like to get a cup of tea?

284
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:26,720
No.

285
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,130
It's just...

286
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:30,690
I wanted to talk for a little while.

287
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:32,100
Then say what you have to say here.

288
00:16:35,830 --> 00:16:36,830
What do I have to do...

289
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:39,600
to win your heart, Jang Mi?

290
00:16:40,570 --> 00:16:41,570
Just tell me anything.

291
00:16:42,110 --> 00:16:43,110
I can do anything.

292
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:45,480
You'd really do anything for me?

293
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:47,440
Are you serious?

294
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:51,150
Yes. Anything for you, Jang Mi.

295
00:16:51,350 --> 00:16:54,390
(General Manager's Office)

296
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:55,750
Then...

297
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:57,820
stop loving me.

298
00:16:58,690 --> 00:17:00,920
The best way you can love me...

299
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:02,830
is by not loving me at all.

300
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:07,560
But you're doing the opposite,
torturing both me and yourself.

301
00:17:07,730 --> 00:17:10,630
- How does that make any sense?
- I'm saying it because it does.

302
00:17:11,370 --> 00:17:13,200
Because of your obsessive love,

303
00:17:13,770 --> 00:17:15,510
you're blind to Seo Rin's love for you.

304
00:17:16,170 --> 00:17:18,710
The love she has for you.

305
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:23,310
- Why bring Seo Rin into this?
- You knew Seo Rin long before me,

306
00:17:24,180 --> 00:17:25,720
and she was in love with you.

307
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,890
Do you even know what that love meant?

308
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:30,020
Seo Rin...

309
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,620
was desperately in love with you.

310
00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:35,190
That girl...

311
00:17:35,890 --> 00:17:37,190
may have seemed to have everything,

312
00:17:37,930 --> 00:17:39,860
but in reality, she had nothing.

313
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:44,230
She suffered from the same loneliness
that you do.

314
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:49,340
That's why she recognized you right away,
and just fell in love.

315
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:54,010
I don't care about Ma Seo Rin.

316
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,610
- I only care about...
- That's my point.

317
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:59,520
Then start caring about Seo Rin
from now on.

318
00:18:00,220 --> 00:18:04,320
That painful loneliness you feel
is something only Seo Rin can understand.

319
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:07,590
Even setting Baek Ho aside,

320
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,660
even if I were reborn,

321
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,060
it's why I could never love you.

322
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,800
Got it?

323
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:16,470
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

324
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:28,980
Oh Jang Mi...

325
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:31,280
knows everything about me.

326
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:33,880
She knows what's in my heart.

327
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:37,050
I'm sorry.

328
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,060
I'm so sorry.

329
00:18:43,660 --> 00:18:44,830
Kang Hyuk, we're in big trouble.

330
00:18:45,430 --> 00:18:48,030
- What is it?
- Seo Rin found out about the necklace.

331
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:49,430
What am I going to do?

332
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:52,740
How could you let her see it?
This is a disaster.

333
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:57,070
I made up an excuse on the spot,

334
00:18:57,710 --> 00:19:01,580
but you know Seo Rin.
She's incredibly perceptive.

335
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,080
I know. This is a huge problem.

336
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:14,760
Hello. Where are you?

337
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:17,790
You're right outside the office?

338
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:23,800
I had a meeting nearby
and thought I'd stop by just in case.

339
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:26,940
Chae Hwa Young is here too.

340
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:30,210
You come here like you own the place,
Lawyer Han.

341
00:19:30,340 --> 00:19:33,680
I was just getting some advice
from Lawyer Han.

342
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,250
My gosh.

343
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:39,050
Are you that embarrassed to admit
that we're dating now?

344
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,320
What? What are you talking about?

345
00:19:41,990 --> 00:19:43,850
It's just...

346
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:46,760
Ms. Chae Hwa Young,
now that you're no longer the CEO,

347
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:49,730
I suppose I can borrow Kang Hyuk, right?

348
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:53,600
Let's go. I love watching your arms
when you drive.

349
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:58,600
Lee Kang Hyuk,
what do you think you're doing?

350
00:19:58,670 --> 00:20:01,710
- Where are you going? We're not finished.
- Let go.

351
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:04,010
- I won't. You let go.
- Let go.

352
00:20:04,010 --> 00:20:05,610
- I won't!
- Let go.

353
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:07,440
- I won't!
- Let go.

354
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:08,510
- I won't.
- Let go!

355
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:09,510
I won't.

356
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,920
My gosh. Hwa Young.

357
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:13,850
What is going on?

358
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:19,760
Well then, I'll leave you two to talk.

359
00:20:21,530 --> 00:20:23,690
- Let's go.
- Shall we, Kang Hyuk?

360
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,160
Han Young Ja.

361
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,570
What on earth was that?

362
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,840
Hwa Young, tell me, what did I just see?

363
00:20:36,570 --> 00:20:37,740
That jerk Lee Kang Hyuk.

364
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:40,010
If he betrays me, it's all over.

365
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:42,550
This is serious. What do I do?

366
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:47,120
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

367
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:51,960
What? Seo Rin.

368
00:20:54,090 --> 00:20:57,730
- I want to go on a picnic with Mom.
- A picnic?

369
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:58,930
Tomorrow's Saturday, you know.

370
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:02,170
A picnic sounds great!
Where are you going? I'll drive.

371
00:21:02,230 --> 00:21:03,700
You're not invited, Baek Ho.

372
00:21:04,370 --> 00:21:06,540
Just Mom, you, and me.

373
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,110
Just the three of us.

374
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:12,440
Okay, let's pack some gimbap
and go on a picnic tomorrow.

375
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:14,680
Gosh, I want to come too.

376
00:21:25,090 --> 00:21:26,090
I want one too.

377
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:31,600
That's a pretty ring.

378
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,000
It is, isn't it?

379
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:37,970
It is pretty. Is it from Baek Ho?

380
00:21:40,140 --> 00:21:42,240
- Yes.
- From two men...

381
00:21:42,740 --> 00:21:43,740
No, I mean...

382
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,980
How does it feel to be loved
by two brothers?

383
00:21:46,340 --> 00:21:49,450
- Seo Rin, please.
- If I'd shown up just 30 minutes later,

384
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,180
you would've married Jun Ho, right?

385
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:56,750
Baek Ho could've been left high and dry,
just like me.

386
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,790
How can you say that?

387
00:21:59,390 --> 00:22:03,790
You're back with us now.
Let's not dwell on the past.

388
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:06,160
It must be nice to be so simple-minded,
Jang Mi.

389
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:08,900
As if you can just not think about it
because you don't want to.

390
00:22:09,570 --> 00:22:10,930
A dozen times a day,

391
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,270
I picture you standing there
in your wedding dress.

392
00:22:13,970 --> 00:22:16,170
But I don't know
if that was me or you anymore.

393
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:17,970
It's all just a blur.

394
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:20,640
The moment you walked in,

395
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:22,650
my heart started beating again.

396
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:25,280
You have no idea how much I blamed myself.

397
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:28,490
If only I'd told Grandfather
the truth sooner,

398
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:32,490
you wouldn't have been held captive
by Chae Hwa Young,

399
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:36,290
and Baek Ho
wouldn't have been put in danger.

400
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:39,030
I'm so sorry, Seo Rin.

401
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:40,930
I mean it.

402
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,330
I know, Jang Mi.

403
00:22:45,270 --> 00:22:46,400
I know you mean it.

404
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:49,770
I was just being difficult. Shit.

405
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:54,440
Open up, Tok Hee.

406
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:05,860
- Tok Hee is pretty. Look at you eat!
- Oh, this is delicious.

407
00:23:08,730 --> 00:23:09,830
Have some more.

408
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:11,930
No, I'll gain weight.

409
00:23:17,170 --> 00:23:18,840
Mom, give me one too.

410
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:21,710
Open up.

411
00:23:22,870 --> 00:23:24,170
Jang Mi is pretty.

412
00:23:24,810 --> 00:23:26,040
Tok Hee is pretty.

413
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:31,010
Mom's been down,
but she seems happy to see you.

414
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:34,350
- Why was she down?
- Tok Hee's grandfather...

415
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:36,690
is mad at Suk Hee.

416
00:23:37,420 --> 00:23:40,360
I couldn't even give Grandfather
his present.

417
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:44,060
He's just preoccupied
with finding his real daughter right now.

418
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:45,560
He's not mad at you, Mom.

419
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,530
Any progress finding his daughter?

420
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:49,900
I don't know.

421
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:50,900
I guess not.

422
00:23:52,170 --> 00:23:53,440
But Mom,

423
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,010
you must have missed me so much
after you lost me.

424
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:59,440
You have no idea.
She was always holding her bunny plush...

425
00:23:59,510 --> 00:24:03,250
- and singing lullabies to it.
- Tok Hee is pretty.

426
00:24:05,950 --> 00:24:07,580
Grandfather said...

427
00:24:08,050 --> 00:24:10,120
he believed that his daughter,
whom he had only held once,

428
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:12,120
had died, and he had long since tried
to put the memory to rest.

429
00:24:12,890 --> 00:24:15,560
But he just found out
she's alive after all this time.

430
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:21,160
Lately, I'm starting to think
Mom's memory might be coming back.

431
00:24:21,870 --> 00:24:24,470
- What?
- She suddenly started reciting the law.

432
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,900
Of course, she went back to her usual self
right after.

433
00:24:28,340 --> 00:24:29,410
Did you take her to a doctor?

434
00:24:29,670 --> 00:24:33,080
- What did the doctor say?
- It's likely dissociative amnesia.

435
00:24:33,510 --> 00:24:38,250
The trauma of losing you back then
was so overwhelming...

436
00:24:38,350 --> 00:24:40,220
that her brain went into survival mode...

437
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,990
and completely shut down
her memories and intellect,

438
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:45,790
and just buried them deep down
in her subconscious.

439
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:48,690
- "Buried them deep down?"
- Right.

440
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:51,660
But now that she has you back in her life,

441
00:24:52,060 --> 00:24:55,730
her subconscious is starting to think,
"It's safe now. My daughter's here."

442
00:24:55,970 --> 00:24:58,240
"I don't have to run
from the pain anymore."

443
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:00,070
It's starting to register.

444
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:04,310
That's why the floodgates to her memories
that were sealed so tight...

445
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:07,480
are slowly starting to open on their own.

446
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:11,980
Mom.

447
00:25:12,380 --> 00:25:14,680
I'm going to stay by your side
from now on.

448
00:25:15,190 --> 00:25:16,220
Shit.

449
00:25:16,450 --> 00:25:17,950
So snap out of it.

450
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:19,220
That's an order.

451
00:25:24,230 --> 00:25:27,400
By the way, is something going on
with Chae Hwa Young?

452
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:32,800
About what the fake Park Young Mi said,

453
00:25:32,870 --> 00:25:36,070
are you saying you investigated
the real Park Young Mi's whereabouts?

454
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:38,240
- Yes, sir.
- And?

455
00:25:38,540 --> 00:25:42,080
So, is the real Park Young Mi my Eun Hye?

456
00:25:42,410 --> 00:25:43,810
The fake Park Young Mi said...

457
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:47,220
Miss Eun Hye went on to high school.

458
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:51,420
So I searched every nearby high school,
but found nothing.

459
00:25:51,820 --> 00:25:54,860
Then search every high school
in the country if you have to.

460
00:25:55,190 --> 00:25:57,960
- Find her, no matter what.
- I already gave that order, sir,

461
00:25:58,730 --> 00:26:00,400
but I did discover one peculiar thing.

462
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:01,970
Peculiar?

463
00:26:02,370 --> 00:26:05,070
- What is it?
- Apparently, the real Park Young Mi...

464
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:07,740
was apparently always seen with a boy.

465
00:26:08,340 --> 00:26:09,370
A boy?

466
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,570
We don't know if he was her older
or younger brother,

467
00:26:12,410 --> 00:26:14,280
but I heard he followed her everywhere
like a shadow.

468
00:26:27,860 --> 00:26:30,630
I wonder if that boy could have been
Oh Bok Gil.

469
00:26:41,670 --> 00:26:44,640
(Chang)

470
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:47,640
If they find out that boy was Oh Bok Gil,

471
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:51,180
they'll know right away
that Jung Suk Hee is Ma Eun Hye.

472
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:54,820
It'll only be a matter of time
until Chairman Ma meets Jung Suk Hee.

473
00:26:56,690 --> 00:27:01,960
<i>When Mommy's in the island's shade</i>

474
00:27:02,930 --> 00:27:07,060
<i>Gathering oysters from the sea</i>

475
00:27:07,130 --> 00:27:08,370
(Chang)

476
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:12,670
Mom, that necklace looks so pretty
with that outfit.

477
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:16,540
This isn't Suk Hee's necklace.

478
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:19,010
Suk Hee's necklace is gone.

479
00:27:21,580 --> 00:27:23,650
Mom, let me see that necklace.

480
00:27:29,250 --> 00:27:30,690
(Chang)

481
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,330
(Chang, Sil)

482
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:40,300
"Chang. Sil."

483
00:27:40,730 --> 00:27:42,470
(Chang, Sil)

484
00:27:43,530 --> 00:27:44,530
Oh my, Seo Rin!

485
00:27:47,470 --> 00:27:48,940
What is this?

486
00:27:49,740 --> 00:27:53,640
This is the necklace my grandfather gave
to his lost daughter, isn't it?

487
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:56,680
Then why do you have both of them?

488
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:00,250
(Chang)

489
00:28:01,580 --> 00:28:02,590
Isn't this...

490
00:28:03,590 --> 00:28:05,090
Mom's necklace?

491
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:10,190
Suk Hee's necklace is gone.

492
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:12,600
Suk Hee doesn't have a necklace.

493
00:28:13,130 --> 00:28:17,370
Then could Mom from the side dish store
be Grandfather's biological daughter?

494
